Nuclear tensions on the Korean Peninsula have diminished since last summer’s Singapore summit between President Trump and North Korea’s Supreme Leader Kim Jong Un.
Unfortunately, that potential deal is where Trump’s foreign policy successes both start and end.
The Trump Doctrine is an “America First” agenda that plays well at home and sounds good on the stump.
At best, it is a shortsighted and dangerous foreign policy play that ultimately creates a global leadership vacuum.
What Trump has not yet realized is that foreign-policy chest beating is not chess playing.